The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal reconstruction, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of statistical mechanical replica method suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistical inference (cs.SI). The application of the scheme to a sparse autoregressive model also suggests a connection to multimedia (cs.MM) as autoregressive models are commonly used in audio and speech processing.
